<div id="review_2591073217" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2591073217" />
    <a title="Terrie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/15236600-terrie"><img alt="Terrie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1552925573p2/15236600.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2591073217?book_show_action=true">Nov 25, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Terrie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Terrie" href="/user/show/15236600-terrie">Terrie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/39102731-long-road-to-mercy">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/15236600-terrie?shelf=timely-nyt-etc-list">timely-nyt-etc-list</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2591073217" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer41351497394836990">I like David Baldacci. I feel like he didn&apos;t write this book. That he got someone else to write it and he just edited, added or told the story and someone else ghost-wrote it.<br/><br/>Atlee was very unlikable for me. She&apos;s a mess and it&apos;s not working in a way that I have empathy for. <br/><br/>Add to that incredible details of.... restoring a mustang, bench pressing/weight lifting, Grand Canyon trails... too many pages of info that didn&apos;t add to this story except for page counts.<br/><br/>I will read more of the Memory Man </span>
  <span id="freeText41351497394836990" style="display:none">I like David Baldacci. I feel like he didn't write this book. That he got someone else to write it and he just edited, added or told the story and someone else ghost-wrote it.<br /><br />Atlee was very unlikable for me. She's a mess and it's not working in a way that I have empathy for. <br /><br />Add to that incredible details of.... restoring a mustang, bench pressing/weight lifting, Grand Canyon trails... too many pages of info that didn't add to this story except for page counts.<br /><br />I will read more of the Memory Man series, but not going to follow Atlee around again.</span>
