<span id="freeTextContainer11212339948336452627">OMG this may have been the worst David Baldacci book I have ever read. What happened Dave? Way over the top with a story which would have been better placed as a James Bond plot (and we know how bad the Bond films were before Daniel Craig came along or Sean Connery I might add). A nuclear device in the Grand Canyon, a plot to nuke North Korea??? Then why was the device in America??? Yes I have to say it was the most over the top plot in Baldacci history. I will never read another Atlee Pine nove</span>
  <span id="freeText11212339948336452627" style="display:none">OMG this may have been the worst David Baldacci book I have ever read. What happened Dave? Way over the top with a story which would have been better placed as a James Bond plot (and we know how bad the Bond films were before Daniel Craig came along or Sean Connery I might add). A nuclear device in the Grand Canyon, a plot to nuke North Korea??? Then why was the device in America??? Yes I have to say it was the most over the top plot in Baldacci history. I will never read another Atlee Pine novel. Maybe next time she'll be sent into space and save the world from an invasion of martians who want to turn us all into babbling idiots who have the rude idea of writing novels about hero's who save the world from nuclear winter!!! Now that's a novel I'd pay to read!!!</span>
