<div id="review_4340003168" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4340003168" />
    <a title="The Cats’ Mother" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5720552-the-cats-mother"><img alt="The Cats’ Mother" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1640916118p2/5720552.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4340003168?book_show_action=true">Nov 26, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="The Cats’ Mother" class="user" itemprop="url" name="The Cats’ Mother" href="/user/show/5720552-the-cats-mother">The Cats’ Mother</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5720552-the-cats-mother?shelf=x-2021-audiobooks">x-2021-audiobooks</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5720552-the-cats-mother?shelf=series">series</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5720552-the-cats-mother?shelf=read-in-2021">read-in-2021</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5720552-the-cats-mother?shelf=action-or-suspense-thrillers">action-or-suspense-thrillers</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5720552-the-cats-mother?shelf=audiobooks">audiobooks</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5720552-the-cats-mother?shelf=bought-e-or-a-books-read">bought-e-or-a-books-read</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4340003168" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13587813551433038280">Long Road to Mercy is the first instalment of the Atlee Pine series, about a young FBI agent whose life has been defined by the unresolved kidnapping of her twin sister Mercy when she was six years old. The book isn’t however about this, but rather a complicated and rather preposterous conspiracy with global implications.<br/>We listened to the audiobook over a couple of car journeys and both enjoyed it.<br/><br/>I mainly picked this because I have a late review copy of book three awaiting my attention, and ha</span>
  <span id="freeText13587813551433038280" style="display:none">Long Road to Mercy is the first instalment of the Atlee Pine series, about a young FBI agent whose life has been defined by the unresolved kidnapping of her twin sister Mercy when she was six years old. The book isn’t however about this, but rather a complicated and rather preposterous conspiracy with global implications.<br />We listened to the audiobook over a couple of car journeys and both enjoyed it.<br /><br />I mainly picked this because I have a late review copy of book three awaiting my attention, and hate reading series out of order. I have enjoyed this author’s earlier series, like the Camel Club &amp; Maxwell &amp; King books, and while I was wary after the rip-off that was the first Puller book, I was ready to give him another go.<br /><br /> I really liked Atlee’s character - she’s a strong (both physically and temperamentally) woman who doesn’t stand for any cr@p from anyone, and the relationship with her secretary, the wannabe PI Carol Blum, was brilliant. The plot was far fetched and hard to believe, especially the resolution, but who reads Baldacci for plausibility? The audiobook narration was perfect - having a male narrator do the relevant voices makes such a difference, and the main reader was easy to listen to.<br />I look forward to continuing Atlee’s story.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13587813551433038280" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


